abstract: WASHINGTON, Dec. 24 -- The Crow Indians arrived in Washington last night accompanied by their agent, Dr. Fred Treon. They come to collect $200,000 from Uncle Sam, damages for the alleged confiscation of large tracts of land in South Dakota, then belonging to their forefathers. The Indians belong to the famous Sioux tribe, and are called Crow Creeks from the country which they inhabit in the Black Hills.
